12/01/2010
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU's new Foreign Affairs chief-designate, Catherine Ashton, called on Monday (January 11th) for an effective strategy to overcome the political stalemate in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). 
During her confirmation hearing at the European Parliament, she rejected the idea of holding a referendum on the status of BiH's entities, as requested by Republika Srpska Prime Minister Milorad Dodik. 
(RTRS, Dnevni Avaz, Fena, FoNet, Politika - 11/01/10)
